The paper proposes an approach for approximate evaluation of queries with probabilistic databases, which is a topic related to database management. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses probabilistic inference and ranking functions, which are topics related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions algorithmic techniques and optimization, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms, and distributed computing, respectively. Therefore, cs.DS and cs.DC are also possible sub-categories.
